                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus><desc>crude drawing in pen of a person</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #19v #28r #35r #48r #57r #118r" facs="003 022 030 037 050 059 120">folss. 1r, 19v, 28r, 35r, 48r, 57r, 118r, </locus> (red and black haräg);
                      <locus target="#6v #12v" facs="009 015">6v, 12v, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#64v #69r #79r" facs="067 071 081">64v, 69r, 79r, </locus> (haräg in blue ink);
                      <locus target="#132r" facs="134">132r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso)" facs="001 002 003">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso)</locus> scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc type="GuestText">
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="003">Fol. 1r</locus> contains an introductory Psalm of the Virgin from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3985Mazmura">Mazmura
                                                  Dǝngǝl</title>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#53r" facs="055">Fol. 53r</locus> a cross-shaped symbol and a two word phrase, “Half of the psalms” mark the midpoint of the Psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–13
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#30v #37v #41v #43r" facs="033 040 044 045">folss. 30v, 37v, 41v, 43r, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#126v #130v" facs="129 133">126v, 130v, </locus>);
                      and interlinearly with the symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be
                      inserted (<locus target="#3v" facs="006"> f. 3v, line 1</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#2r #12r #15r #21r #25r" facs="004 014 017 023 027">2r, 12r, 15r, 21r, 25r, </locus>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#63r #72r" facs="065 074">63r, 72r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is
                          addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an
                          appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the
                          line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size
                          at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#9v #10r #27v" facs="012 030">fols. 9v, 10r, 27v</locus>)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
